track_notes: There does not appear to be a trail to the peak.  This route is a bushwhack / scramble up the Northern side.  It is short but steep.  When I did it there was snow which added to the challenge.
This was our path up the hill.

My wife,me,son and dog went straight up the front from the campground between two towers of rocks with gaps. Gap on the far left is passable. Looked to steep to go back that same way with the son so we came down the back side. This way was a lot easier but adds a few miles to the adventure. (Also mapping system shows arrows going backwards)

This route begins at a junction with the Arizona Trail at GPS 32.33603,-110.72020. The trail to the summit is easy to follow at the beginning but gets more difficult to follow as it gets steeper. Look for an opening between 2 columns of rocks (see photos) to access the summit this way.
track_title: Prison Camp Ridge via trail UP

track_notes: My descent from Prison Camp Ridge follows the same trail I used to ascend. The length shows longer than my UP track because I ended the DOWN track where I parked near Mt Lemmon Hwy.
track_title: Prison Camp Ridge via trail DOWN
